          content: `<p>Every crypto trader has their favorite metrics:</p><ul><li>Market cap ("this is undervalued!")</li><li>Trading volume ("look at the interest!")</li><li>Holder count ("adoption is growing!")</li><li>Social mentions ("it's trending!")</li></ul><p>None of these predict price reliably. They're lagging indicators at best, manipulated at worst.</p><p>There's only one metric that matters: <strong>real utility demand</strong> - are people buying the token to <em>use</em> it, or just to flip it? As we covered in <a href='/blog/tokens-that-print-money-utility-value/'>tokens that print money</a>, revenue-backed utility is the foundation.</p>`,
