          title: "The Utility Demand Metric",
          content:
            "<h2><strong>The Utility Demand Metric</strong></h2><p>Real utility demand asks: <strong>Are people acquiring this token because they need it for something?</strong></p><p>Examples of utility demand:</p><ul><li><strong>ETH:</strong> Need it to pay gas fees</li><li><strong>BNB:</strong> Need it for fee discounts and launchpad access</li><li><strong>LINK:</strong> Protocols need it to use Chainlink oracles</li><li><strong>$IPO:</strong> Need it to access pre-IPO deals</li></ul><p>Examples of speculation demand:</p><ul><li>DOGE: Pure speculation, no use case</li><li>Most meme coins: Buying to sell higher</li><li>Dead L1s: Nobody uses the chain</li></ul><p>Tokens with utility demand have a floor. Tokens without it can go to zero.</p>",
